 A team of seven officers from Nemato led by the branch commander, Detective Sergeant Stewart Abrahams, gathered information on their outstanding suspects for March and April and went on a spree since 02:00 on Thursday morning. "They arrested 22 suspects for various contact crimes," said police spokesperson, Captain Mali Govender. "15 suspects, including four females have face charges of serious assault; three males face charges of Breach of protection order; three suspects were linked and arrested on a charge of Housebreaking and theft." Captain Govender said that one male faces a charge of malicious damage to property. "The suspects are aged between 16 and 54." All suspects will appear in the Port Alfred Magistrate's Court this week. 